ished friday on the Norfork. The Norfork was running 2 units and we had to wait for the water to drop out. We were a little concerned about trying to wade the river on 2 units so we wound up sitting on the back for about an hour to let the water drop out. Rob's patience paid off with 2 nice rainbows over 20&quot;.<br>
<br>
The next morning we headed for the White. Since we had already topped his personal best, we were just going to try to catch another big one. Rob's first fish of the day was a nice 25&quot; male rainbow that weighed around 9lbs on the net scale. <br>
<br>
I had used all the tricks in my bag at this point. We headed to the lower White on Sunday. We picked out a nice shoal and rob tied on a &quot;Trout Crack&quot;. Within about an hour he had caught 20+ fish and showed no signs of slowing down. We finished up the rest of the day casting to a brown that was 40-42&quot; probably. We never did hook the fish although our hearts stopped a couple of times when his mouth opened as our fly floated past.<br>
<br>
Well done Rob. You are an excellent fly fisher no doubt.<br>
<br>
John<br>
